gomodel:SYNGO_1255  a    owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment     "Rationale: The authors use the lamprey reticulospinal synapse. They inject an antibody (function blocking) into the pre synapse. They stimulate the neurons for 30 min at 5 Hz to activate SV exo/endocytosis. In the antibody injected neurons there is a large accumulation of clathrin-coated tubules.\n\n15/8/2017 Pim\n- The lamprey accession was found via Blast of the human EHD1 protein. Experimental description: From the abstract, \"We have investigated the role of an EHD1/3 ortholog (l-EHD) in the lamprey giant reticulospinal synapse\"" ;
        lego:modelstate  "production" ;
        dc:contributor   "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date          "2017-10-10" ;
        dc:title         "SYNGO_BP_1255" ;
        pav:providedBy   "https://syngo.vu.nl" .

